The state-owned  Japan  Bank for
International Cooperation pledged a $23.5 million grant to fund
a water project in  Jordan , the Jordan Times reported today.  The agreement is due to be signed later this month, the
newspaper said, citing Planning Minister Jaafar Hassan, who
returned yesterday from a visit to Japan. The Asian country is
also considering a loan to support Jordanâ€™s budget, the paper
